records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, burglary.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 through 5.  Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years, consecutive to the jail sentence presently being served on 15 CM 302.
Conditions of probation:
1) spend four (4) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, consecutive to the straight jail sentence imposed on 15 CM 302;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Provide DNA sample;
6) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/work search;
7) No contact with Christopher Loucks, Brittany Ramon, Taylor Baxter, Bruce Suettinger, Manitowoc Walmart, Manitowoc Walgreens, Charles Adams, Tany Pivonka-Dewane and contact with Lauren Free will be as directed by the agent;
8) Pay court costs;
9) Pay supervision fees;
10) Pay restitution as follows:
- $1,417.94 to Bruce Suettinger at 6201 CTH O, Two Rivers, WI;
- $354.83 to Walmart Restitution Recovery at 702 SW 8th Street, Bentonville, AK 72716-0815; joint and several with Lauren Free;
- $115.87 to Walmart Restitution Recovery;
- $120.00 to Charles Adams at 2514 45th Street, Two Rivers, WI 54241;
- $514.50 to Associated Bank at 1121 Franklin Street, Manitowoc, WI; joint and several with Brittany Ramon, Christopher Loucks and Taylor Baxter;
- $11.59 to Two Rivers Piggly Wiggly at 2300 Forest Avenue, Two Rivers, WI 54241.
Restitution is to be paid at the minimum rate of $75.00 per month when the defendant is not serving the jail terms.  The defendant will make payments out of employment proceeds earned while on Huber release to satisfy this restitution obligation.
The $500.00 cash bail is to be applied to restitution owing to Bruce Suettinger.
